cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR

The paper deals with analyzing learner interaction with an e-learning application, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a Hidden Markov Model for modeling the interaction suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of mouse movement data may also suggest the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
